body:
It was just an attempt to scale the output to a range that is most commonly used.

But I was never sure it was the right thing to do anyways. And it can however easily be added as a formatter by those who so choose.

From the unit tests:
```
        @{duration = "0:0:21"; expectedResult = "00:21.000"}
        @{duration = "1:14:21"; expectedResult = "01:14:21"}
        @{duration = "1.1:14:21"; expectedResult = "1.01:14:21"}
```

That is remove the hours from most of the execution times. 

This may be to opinionated, and based on my usage. I'll remove it after PSConfEU.
